CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 22, 1955, pg. 12, reads: "Delta Luncheon Scene - Snapped at the Greene Hearthe are some of the Delta Sigma Theta Sorors and members of the Delta Patroness Board who were honored last Sunday at the forty-fourth anniversary of the founding of Delta. Shown, left center, backs to the cameras, are Sorors Mary Baltimore, president of Alpha Epsilon; Vivian Swain, president of Mu, and Laura Little, president of Theta Chapter. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Women seated at banquet tables, including left center, backs to the cameras, are Sorors Mary Baltimore, president of Alpha Epsilon; Vivian Swain, president of Mu, and Laura Little, president of Theta Chapter, gathered in the Greene Hearth for the forty-fourth anniversary of the Delta Sigma Theta sorority
